I had the pleasure of working for Express Employment for Suzanne and John.  I had two interviews within two weeks and were offered both positions the next business day.  Suzanne is very professional, she made sure to set up interviews for positions of my interest but also provided other opportunities without being aggressive or tried to convince me but simply provide additional options.  John helped me with the decision making of which company would be best for me.  After I started employment, both John and Suzanne would continue to communicate and made sure I was comfortable.  While picking up my first paycheck, John took the time to meet me in person and congratulate me and continued to be there when I had questions or concerns.

Express Employment on Flanders Drive in Mira Mesa has a feeling of comfort, compassion, professionalism, and it felt like home.  Everyone there has been great, on point, and communication is on point.  I would strongly recommend Express if asked which agency to sign up with.<//text>

Their customer service is absolutely horrible. I swapped to an 11 Pro last week. Since the swap from my XR my signal has been horrible. Average downloads of 2Mbps, and upload of .4Mbps.

If you research online this a widespread issue with 11, and 11pro‚Äôs. My satisfaction guarantee for the phone is January 25th. It‚Äôs currently January 7th.

This store would not swap my phone because diagnostics showed everything checked out, even though the speed tests showed very low.

They directed me to the Apple Store, so I went. The Apple Store wanted to swap my SIM, and restore the phone as new. Which means I have to download all my apps again, re-categorize, and group everything. They wanted to eliminate software as the issue. If that didn‚Äôt resolve the issue they would swap the phone. I was not willing to do this, because if software is the issue, then the issue would have existed on my XR. It didn‚Äôt.

Went back to the store, and they said they could swap the phone, but they would have to charge me the restocking fee of $45. I should not have to pay this when the device is not functioning properly.

I chatted with Sprint online, and they are immediately sending me a replacement, and return package, without charging me a restocking fee. This appears to be an issue of the store not wanting this return, and replace, to show up on their bottom line. This is terrible customer service. They will never receive another dollar from me.</review>

< Text>
Tolowa is a great place to hike.  It has a lot of variety from the beach to the forest with ponds scattered around.  It also has an Elk herd of over 100 that you see ever now and then.  It is also the only place I've ever been close to a Porcupine.  Keep you eye out for giant ant mounds as well.< /Text>

< resp>

<UserId.>117488642041036826638</UserId.><date>1559448084568<//date>< Text>
It's removed from the mainstream, it's beautiful, be forewarned though that it gets COLD! And quick. Plus, in the summer, the mosquitoes are thick in the trees, the wind is blowing so much and so hard it is probably the equivalent to a windsurfer in their ultimate happy place. It's intense. The only amenities that are available is a rest stop style outhouse. It is way off the main road and you might have a couple of misses at first when you try to find it. Unless you have gps or something like that. Last thing I will add is that it is a historical site in the local eyes as the area between Brookings and Humboldt county are  native american indian ancestral lands with their own history to share that is something that, if given the opportunity to learn more about it from the tribespeople you should count yourself among the very few gifted with the knowledge and should treat it respectfully. That respect should please find it's way into how the protected watershed/wetlands and state/national park/dunes area are treated, as well as our everyday life.< /Text>

< review>
Overlooked by most , this wonder of the area is not given the credit it deserves! Absolutely beautiful! I recommend dead lake early in the morning to see river otters, the loop at the end of old mill rd to the big dune, and the yontucket area (1/2mi walk from the end of lake earl dr) and go to the ocean, the smith or the dunes!</review>

<rating>5<//rating><text>#KiaForLife

Over the last 12 years Rally Kia has been my go to for any of my car needs. The last few years were a bit rough to say the least. However, I cannot express the amount of appreciation and TRUST I have again with them as they have come under new management.

My 2018 Optima was recently totaled. The interior handled like a champ - 3 airbags deploying and all! Walking away with soreness and only bruises, I was somewhat reluctant to head back to this particular dealer due to the decline in customer service over the last few years.

Making my way in to double check on last minute questions before I headed to a competitor dealer, I was greeted by ROBERT WALLS. I had worked with him once earlier in the year but never saw him again and assumed he left the company. After explaining my previous incidents and issues with Rally, Robert apologized and explained that he would do his best to amend my views and rectify a situation to which I had no fault in. Because of his demeanor and WILLINGNESS to HELP me, I toured the lot with him.

He then had SHAINA, a member of his team, take me on a test drive of a car similar to what I had lost. She was informative and beyond kind. I appreciated being treated like a person, not just dollar signs. Although the drive went well, I remained skeptical and kept "one foot out the door".

ROBERT WALLS came into the office to present a great deal but unfortunately I was still a bit short. He left for a few minutes and came back with a deal that RESTORED MY FAITH in Kia's customer service, rectified the finance issue caused by previous management and HELPED me to drive off in a new car!

Words cannot express the amount of GRATITUDE I HAVE FOR ROBERT WALLS, SHAINA, SANDRO GUZMAN, BRYAN ARANA and the AMAAAAAZZZZZING team at Palmdale RALLY KIA!!!!!! My husband is due for a car soon and I know WE WILL be coming back! I am PROUD to have my 5th Kia and looking forward to my husband getting his 2nd!

THANK YOU, THANK YOU, THANK YOU, you guys!!!!!
BEST. EXPERIENCE. EVER!< /text>< Pictures>

< Review>
So this place... Where to begin. Bought a Cadenza from these guys in February. Went in looking at a Stinger to begin with. Looked at the numbers and my trade situation. Against my better judgement I did the deal. Mainly because they weren't willing to get to a reasonable place on the Stinger and I kinda wanted to get rid of my trade. So, a few weeks go by and they tell me they need to rewrite the contract because there need to be a service agreement in it. They wanna raise the price of my monthly by $40. I tell them just give me my trade back. They settle on like $10 a month more. Which even then I should have just given them the car back and taken my trade.
Here is where it gets screwy as if it wasn't already. The check for my trade payoff that the dealership sent to the finance company bounced. Yes that's right it bounced. So did the second check they sent to pay it off. I email the owner. I go down there. He says my checks don't bounce. Well obviously they do if the lienholder to my trade tells me that it bounced. So I got to make 2 extra payments on my trade in addition to paying for my new car. In the end they gave me money back for all that. Which is the only reason they get 2 stars.
I have since gotten rid of that Cadenza because it wasn't what I wanted to begin with. That was a month ago. Gave these guys the paperwork to cancel my service plan that they made me get about a month ago as well. They still haven't cancelled it nor sent me a check for the refund.
Other reviews say walking into this dealership is like walking in on a mob boss meeting. They are spot on. There is never anyone there on the lot looking because they don't wanna deal with the tactics sales uses. Once you are in there they will basically grind you down until you submit. Best thing I can say is if you bring a trade make sure to get your keys and registration back as soon as they are done appraising it so you can leave at will. Not sure how these guys are best of AV 2018 dealership.
If you really want a Kia try CarPros Kia. Never had any issues when I bought my Optima there. It was in and out not much haggling at all and took about 2 hours.</Review>

<Date>1491932566833< /Date><rate>3</rate>< text>
I've tried their crepes and their sandwiches, and while both were adequate, neither was particularly great, and there's a lot of great food nearby. I don't recall the crepe in detail, but the avocado sandwich was basic, on white toast, and felt more like a snack than a meal. To be fair, the price was modest too.

I'm living less than a block away, but I rarely go here, because I've always come away underwhelmed. I'd go again if invited by a friend who likes it, but otherwise, probably not.< /text>

< Text>
I was pleasantly surprised the first tome I visited this restaurant, looking at it from the street, you would not expect what is inside, it is a peaceful ambiance as soon as you walk through the doors, the servers are soft spoken, which it goes with the ambiance :)  the food is delicious, it is not greasy and the sauces are not heavy, I do not drink sodas, or sweet drinks, so I ordered a coconut water, which they serve on the actual fresh coconut. it was amazingly delicious, and after I was done with the water, I scooped up the coconut meat, it was so fresh, tender and creamy, their pineapple fried rice its delicious, I also recommend the kung pao chichen level 5 (spiciness) I love it spicy, they also have great weekdays lunch deals under $8, I highly recommend this restaurant, I just gave it 4 stars, because there is always room for improvement.  over all GREAT EXPERIENCE!</Text>

A full replacement of my upper teeth was more expensive than I really wanted to pay but once I compared the cost of mini implants to regular implants, I was convinced it was worth it. I decided on the nicest material because I really wanted them to look natural and stay with me for a long time.

The process wasn‚Äôt perfectly easy, there was some problems with my temporary bite and it caused some extra visits. My temporary broke on Christmas Eve and I called the answering service. Someone met me at the office within 30 minutes and spent hours fixing my temporary and ensuring that I could eat Christmas dinner with my family. It was a huge deal to me. I chose sedation for the initial procedure and it was way easier than I thought it would be. Pain was minimal after the procedure was done on Saturday I was back at work on Monday.

After about 6 weeks from the start I have the kind of teeth that people notice and make comments about. Teeth that I can actually eat with. I am so proud of my new smile and I actually open my mouth to talk.

< text>
I live in the Bay Area and I travel to Sacramento to see Dr. Smith. I have been her patient for over 11 years and no matter where I live in California, I make the trip to see Dr. Smith. Family n friends all think I'm crazy and try to recommend other dentists but none of them live up to Dr. Smith.

I have a severe phobia of dentists, struggle with anxiety and have a panic attack disorder. Dr. Smith's sedation services make dentistry possible for me despite my limitations. Other sedation dentists want to use IV sedation but Dr. Smith only uses the most minimally evasive options in all her work, including sedation. I know I'm a difficult patient but Dr. Smith makes me feel like her favorite patient and I am so grateful to have a dentist like her.

I tell her all the time, "If it wasn't for you, I would have no teeth." She smiles n laughs but it's true! < text>
Do NOT, under ANY circumstances, give this company any of your business. My husband made a reservation for a car and carseat rental over the phone days ago. Our flight was scheduled to arrive at 10:10 pm and the representative from Alamo assured him that they would have someone stay two hours late to make sure that we could have our reservation at this time. My husband double, triple, and quadruple checked that this would happen, and over and over he was promised that someone would stay late to give us our rental.

Well WE. WERE. LIED. TO. Our flight came in as scheduled at 10:10, we walked to this location where our reservation was made and it is closed! No one is here. My husband called the company and was simply told that they close at 10, even though we have a reservation with a confirmation number saying otherwise.

The representative said that we could pick up a car tomorrow, but that is not an option, seeing as how we are now stranded at the airport parking garage at 11 pm with our 1 year old child. Apparently they expect us to sleep in the parking lot with our baby while we wait for them to fulfill their broken promises.

This awful depraved company has single handedly put my family in a terribly unsafe position. If a business following through on their word means anything to you whatsoever, I implore you to stay far far away from Alamo Rent A Car.

UPDATE:
I see that the owner has asked for us to email Alamo so that they could ‚Äúlook into this further.‚Äù My husband actually already emailed them last night (we had plenty of time while we were stuck at the airport alone until 2 am while we waited for my aunt with nightblindness to get out of bed, unload her car, fill it with gas, and brave the night to come rescue us) and we received a lackluster canned response trying to place the blame on us for being late to pick up the reservation. Yes you heard me right, even though we gave the employee our flight information when we made the reservation (which had our arrival time after 10 pm) and we were assured that someone would stay after, because their employee did not record this it is now somehow our fault that this company stranded our family at the airport parking garage in the middle of the night with no option to take an Uber (because we were renting a car seat) and no option to go with another rental company because they were all closed. Thank you for your inspired customer service, Alamo.</text>

Most importantly, the staff was so so soooo FRIENDLY and HELPFUL. They even hooked me up with a sweet deal and gave me recommendations on how to do it for the future. There was no BS. I was pleasantly surprised by my whole experience and can not recommend this place enough. I wish I remembered the name of the man who helped me so I could give him a shout out!
I will add that I only picked up here. So I cannot attest to the drop off process though people looked happy.< /review>

<Gmap_id>0x80dcdef72d684abd:0xe2c3d7e083d3af52< /Gmap_id><resp>{'time': 1540924056632, 'text': 'Dayna, we would like to look into this further. Kind regards, Michael'}<//resp>< Text>
Rented full size car for 1 day trip up to Fresno. Car was great. I had called Alamo Customer Service line before I reached the airport to ask about their credit card policy and if there was a deposit when checking out the car. I was told that if I had not pre-paid for the reservation then they will be authorizing my credit card for the amount of the reservation. No additional deposit required. However, at the front counter the girl who checked me in didn't mention any deposit, just asked for my ID and credit card and off we were to get our car in less than 5 minutes. I only noticed the $200 additional deposit when I logged onto to my credit card company and saw the authorization. Then upon returning the vehicle we were running about 20 minutes behind. I had return time of 12 noon. It was 20 minutes to noon when I was filling up the car and I called Alamo and spoke to another customer support person who advised me that I had a 30 min grace period so I should be fine. I arrive at 12:17p and was given a receipt which had a 2 hour charge. I asked the guy who checked me out what it was for and he explained that I actually picked up the car at 11:30a and so it was due in by 11:30a. I asked about the 30 min grace period and he didn't know what to say. He was kind enough to fix it but had I not looked at my receipt I wouldn't have noticed the extra charge. Not happy with this transaction. Probably won't rent from them again.< /Text>

<Rating>4</Rating>< Text>
Nissan Rogue -- Black.  Well-crafted interior.  Spacious.  Ample seat for any adult driver/passenger.  Very good fuel economy and power-performance.  The seat warmer switch is awkwardly placed; my hand accidentally turned it on when I was opening the center storage console because of its low location.  It would be better placed on the dashboard.

The fob needs to have a chain or tie that the renter can attach to something.  Since I use an actual key on my own vehicle, I am not accustomed to the fob, and kept forgetting in which compartment of my purse I put it in; plus, it always made me nervous that I might have misplaced it because it is an unattached, small object.

Customer service at John Wayne airport is as-expected.  Staff try to be nice, but are generally unpolished in pulling this off.  They come across as fawning, patronizing.  Speed of service during the off-peak hours that I checked out and checked in the vehicle was fast, as it should be.< /Text>

< Text>
First let me say I've rented here 30 times so far this year.
The people are generally polite, biggest issue so far is that many times the cars aren't cleaned well. Worst issue was an OPEN bottle of alcohol left in the car..

However this time after turning my car in on a Sunday night, I go to switch the charge to my debit card, as I usually do.
The charge is approx 50 bucks.
I go to the counter, hand the guy my debit and he says all set.

Next morning, I look at my account and apparently "All SET" means charging my card twice for $210.00 and $310.00. Posted charges, not holds.

Monday, call Alamo. Get told the location has to fix it and they will call me. Nobody calls.

Tuesday First thing, call again. Get the run around and told it's probably my fault. Riiiight. Literally every way to blame me. Finally they will call the location again. 6 hours later I get a call, I miss the call but call back shortly.

Again hear about a half dozen ways it's probably my fault. Finally after about 40 minutes the guy seems to understand what's going on. But cant help. Someone else has to and will call me back.

Wednesday nothing.

Thursday. Call again. Again get the run around and that its probably my fault. Worst problem with the 800 number customer service, they seem automatically be trained to not listen and blame you.

You must have had more than 1 rental. NOPE
You must have damaged it. NOPE
You must have not put gas in. NOPE
It's only a hold. NOPE (after telling them it was a switch to a different card)

Finally I get transferred to "escalations"
Where again, I get told it's my fault.

After beating my head against a brick wall... Im told "you could always just dispute it instead of keep calling".

Really? Basically telling the customer to "eff off and fix it yourself" Thats ridiculous customer service. Thanks for telling me I can go drive to my bank and waste even more of my time fixing YOUR MISTAKE myself.

So now a District Manager is supposed to call and that was 6 hours ago.. Not holding my breath at this point.
Edit...8pm 11 hours after I was supposed to get a call, no call. Good thing I didn't hold my breath. I'd be dead, and still out 500 bucks.

EDIT 2...  Noon in Friday.
Still no call from the District Manager or the Location manager.
Called Customer (no) Service again. And again it's my fault.

4...now 5 days 6
...now 7 people and no results. Probably the most inept customer service across the board,  I've ever come across.

Hopefully if you rent here you don't have any issues, because if you do, you are in for a clown show.
I've been a district manager myself for several retailers and had to deal with similar issues countless times. Never has it taken me 4 days (and counting) to address a customer and get the issue resolved.</Text>

< review>
When are flight arrived at John Wayne Airport we proceeded to the baggage claim to get our bags.  The Alamo rent a car office was a short walk outside to the rental car parking lot.  There were 2 people ahead of us and just waited about 5 minutes to get our vehicle.  Check in was very easy (since I did the reservation online before we left for our vacation) she just had to re-verify all of the information and then we signed a few documents.  She asked me if I wanted to upgrade (I believe because they did not have the car available that we reserved online), I declined the upgrade (which I would have been charged for) and when we got outside to get our keys they ended up upgrading us, so instead of getting the Toyota Corolla that we reserved online we ended up with a Dodge Charger (which was very nice!).  The car had only 8123 miles and we did not have any issues through our rental.  We returned the rental car to the Airport in Las Vegas (which was set up when I reserved the rental car online).  Drop off was very easy, just drove up to the drop off point, unloaded our vehicle and they came over checked over the car and gave me a receipt.  I noticed that I was charged an extra $22.78 for a tourism fee....I am not sure why....but I am going to get with AMX to see if they will adjust the fee for me.  Overall we were very happy with the rental and would rent from Alamo again.<//review>

<Rating>2< /Rating><text>Always rent with Alamo through AAA or Costco Travel. Never had problems until this time.

Upon arrival to the rental counter at John Wayne Airport, the poor girl at the counter was by herself, not a soul to help her.  There were about 10 people in line.  It took forever to get to the front of the line. When I finally got to the front of the line, I had a sunburn on the back of my neck from the sun blaring through the glass windows and ceiling around the rental counter area. These kind of things start your vacation off on the wrong side of the road. Lady was friendly and welcoming upon reaching the counter.  She's good.  I would be irritated if I were her.

My rate was all good, then I was offered the gas for 1/2 a tank for $18.00 total. Information given was that gas was very expensive in LA, which I believed and turns out was correct. I agreed to the gas part as we were driving for 5 days only a couple miles from the hotel to Disneyland Park round trip then to Los Angeles on our last day. 1/2 a tank was exactly where we landed upon returning to LAX late in the evening. That is where we were met by some crazed ALAMO return agent outside that just had it in him to argue with me that night. He informed me that instead of the $18.00 for a 1/2 tank, I was being charged about $40.00 or more for the gas. I explained about the $18.00 agreement.  He said that didn't matter anymore because it wasn't on my agreement and I had been upgraded for free so the car type no longer qualified for the $18.00 gas promo. I told him "no, it's on my agreement, and I didn't ask for the upgrade, the lady in the garage at Anaheim just gave it to me because there were no compact cars ready." He kept insisting that I agreed to the upgrade vs. the gas promo.  Should that matter: I didn't know it was one or the other. Never had that problem before. But to my amazement, the gas information wasn't on the contract. Now is when I started to curse in my head that I didn't double check it before I walked away from the counter.  I kept saying to him, that it was agreed upon in Anaheim, and he kept trying to tell me "no, that is not what you are paying." I argued for awhile, but ended up giving up as I didn't want to spoil my last day of vacation. I just walked away.

I come home to check my credit card bill and it was only charged for the original $69.58. WTH!? So what was the purpose of the guy in LA treating me like an idiot and wanting to argue with me.  Shoot, I work for a major hotel chain and can't believe that this guy argued with me...a customer.  If I did that, I would not have a job.

Next car reservation has been made with another major car agency.  I will give them a try.  Let's see if they want to argue with me. One wrong episode and I don't usually return to a business. Save my sanity.</text><pics>None</pics>< Response>

<Review>Booked a car online through Orbitz in a package deal (i.e., air, hotel, car). Arrived and was able to immediately speak with an agent to get the paperwork done, which was quick and straightforward. Went to pick up the car and was offered a "free" upgrade, not sure from what I was upgraded to. Alamo staff were friendly and professional and the whole process went smoothly. I thought the pricing was pretty reasonable as well.

The only comments I would make, and these are relatively minor, at John Wayne Airport I think then need better signage outside to locate the pick up location. The direx from the Alamo desk agent were really unclear, and there is little if any signage outside, had to ask a cop.

Second, I asked about direx to a nearby hotel, no one truly knew and the direx I got from Alamo at the pick up point were so vague they were entirely not helpful... if you don't know where something is, don't send a customer off with bad direx.

Given this, it would be helpful if they had GPSs available for rental as well, this would have been a great opportunity to "up sell".

But all in all, a pretty good experience.</Review><Gmap_id>0x80dcdef72d684abd:0xe2c3d7e083d3af52</Gmap_id><Resp>None</Resp></record>
